menu "OPSEC Features"

    config OPSEC_HMAC_TOPIC
        bool "Use HMAC-derived opaque MQTT topics"
        default y if WOL_PROFILE_HARDENED
        default n
        help
            Derives the MQTT command and response topic names from
            HMAC-SHA256 of the chip MAC and a 32-byte secret stored
            in NVS.  The secret is generated randomly on first boot.

            Result: topics appear as 16-character hex strings
            (e.g. "d4f3a891c02e57b3") with no identifiable relation
            to Wake-on-LAN or to the device.

            Derivation:
              digest        = HMAC-SHA256(secret, chip_mac_bytes)
              command_topic = hex(digest[0..7])    // 16 hex chars
              response_topic= hex(digest[8..15])   // 16 hex chars

            In STANDARD builds the topics are plain strings:
              command_topic  = "wol/<MAC>"
              response_topic = "wol/<MAC>/r"

    config OPSEC_TOTP
        bool "Require TOTP-signed payloads (anti-replay)"
        default y if WOL_PROFILE_HARDENED
        default n
        depends on OPSEC_HMAC_TOPIC
        help
            Requires incoming MQTT payloads to include a valid
            RFC 6238 TOTP suffix in addition to the target MAC.

            Payload format (without TOTP):
              "AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF"

            Payload format (with TOTP):
              "AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF:123456"

            The 6-digit code is validated against a 20-byte TOTP
            seed stored in NVS (generated randomly on first boot).
            The acceptance window is T-1, T, T+1 (±60 seconds) to
            tolerate clock drift between the ESP32 and the sender.

            The ESP32 must have synchronized its clock via SNTP
            before TOTP validation is active.  Until clock sync,
            TOTP payloads are rejected and a warning is logged.

            The companion trigger script (scripts/wake_hardened.sh) handles
            TOTP generation automatically.

    config OPSEC_TOTP_STEP_SEC
        int "TOTP time step in seconds"
        default 30
        range 15 60
        depends on OPSEC_TOTP
        help
            Duration of each TOTP window.  RFC 6238 mandates 30 s.
            Matching the sender and the ESP32 to the same value is
            required — do not change unless you also update the
            trigger script.

    config OPSEC_TOTP_DIGITS
        int "TOTP code length (digits)"
        default 6
        range 6 8
        depends on OPSEC_TOTP
        help
            Number of digits in the TOTP code.  6 is the RFC 6238
            standard.  8 gives a larger code space but is less
            convenient to type manually.

    config OPSEC_SNTP_SERVER
        string "SNTP server hostname"
        default "pool.ntp.org"
        depends on OPSEC_TOTP
        help
            NTP server used to synchronise the ESP32 clock for TOTP
            validation.  pool.ntp.org resolves to the nearest
            Stratum 2 server.  Replace with a local NTP server or a
            trusted public one (e.g. "time.cloudflare.com") if
            preferred.

    config OPSEC_TEST
        bool "Expose internal functions for unit testing"
        default n
        help
            Exposes totp_at_counter_for_test() in opsec.h.
            Never enable in production builds.

endmenu
